			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I would like to propose something very interesting.  I am proposing the new concept of &quot;special moves&quot; hotkey commands. <br>  <br> I realized that the fight in everquest lacked beauty, nothing alatming, but i see that we all could benifit improvment. <br>  <br> the concept goes as follows... <br> the same way some classes use &quot;kick&quot; as a special moves, they could also use , for example, a &quot;thunder slash&quot; hot key command that would be an all new animation of the character jumping and landing on the floor while slashing his enemy(off sourse these special moves would have a reuse time factor)....continnuing with this exemple...that &quot;special move&quot; would be acquiered by earning new lvls....and practicing it the same way some practice kick....Some special moves could be acquiered by doing quest and meeting specific guild master.  Also, certain special moves could be only done with a 1hs or with a 2hs, or with certain specific quest weapons. Tha could open a TREMENDOUS number of possibilities...the fights in everquest would have an all new visage... <br>  <br> in the forset of kelethin we could assist to fights so beautyfull, they would better then those seen in soulBlade etc.... <br>  <br> some might say:&quot;warriors already have diciplines!&quot; it is true....but diciplines ar basicly the modifications of statistics...you dont REALLY controle them.....the concept i propose is more concret..(sticking with the kick command) <br>  <br>  <br> (excuse my mediocre english, it is not my primary language)....i will and this post by giving you some ideas <br>  <br> ...spinning slash <br> ...power crush <br> ...dual weild rain <br> ...2hander thrust <br> ...etc <br>  <br> my name is Daniel Laine..also known as Dracian Drak'Odynn. <br> 
